issue.title: Infracost commands do not exit with correct error codes
issue.body:
When running in terragrunt project an error resolving dependency may occur (nothing to do with infracost, no complains here :) ).

The `infracost breakdown` command will then exit with zero code, thus making it hard to figure out why there is no cost estimation report data (shows no changes since diff cannot do anything useful).

Example error observed in contents of a failed run for `infracost breakdown` -> infracost-base.json:

```
"metadata":{"path":"/tmp/base/.","type":"error","errors":[{"code":0,"message":"Error processing module at '/tmp/base/aks/terragrunt.hcl'. How this module was found: dependency of module at '/tmp/base/livedemo/shared/auto_scaling_nodepools'. Underlying error: Error reading file at path /tmp/base/aks/terragrunt.hcl: open /tmp/base/aks/terragrunt.hcl: no such file or directory","data":null}]}
```

which is a result of a bug in terragrunt (and I have to fix it by using merge_strategy = "deep", the fix actually works, again no complains here against infracost binary): 

https://github.com/gruntwork-io/terragrunt/issues/2510

The issue is, when this happens `infracost breakdown` command simply does exit 0, where I expect it to actually error and not have to handle this situation myself by some parsing of the output (infracost-base.json) or having to inspect artifacts in my CI system.

NOTE: I have fixed the terragrunt issue and infracost works just fine so the estimation feature works excellently in a terragrunt project , which is just wonderful - thanks for your hard work guys. 

Pretty please if there could be at least an option to pass a flag argument to infracost commands to exit 1 on any error, or just do that always.

Thanks,

Tom

issue.title: Add support for AWS CloudHSM
issue.body:
Please consider adding support for AWS CloudHSMs in both the product and also into the usage file. These are relatively expensive resources and we want to make sure we flag their creation.

Terraform resources:
https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/aws/latest/docs/resources/cloudhsm_v2_cluster
https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/aws/latest/docs/resources/cloudhsm_v2_hsm

Pricing: https://aws.amazon.com/cloudhsm/pricing/

Example pricing: $1.45/hr in Oregon and $1.59/hr in London.

pull_request.title: chore(deps): bump google.golang.org/grpc from 1.55.0 to 1.56.3
pull_request.body:
Bumps [google.golang.org/grpc](https://github.com/grpc/grpc-go) from 1.55.0 to 1.56.3.
Release notes

Sourced from google.golang.org/grpc's releases.

Release 1.56.3

Security

  • server: prohibit more than MaxConcurrentStreams handlers from running at once (CVE-2023-44487)

    In addition to this change, applications should ensure they do not leave running tasks behind related to the RPC before returning from method handlers, or should enforce appropriate limits on any such work.

Release 1.56.2

  • status: To fix a panic, status.FromError now returns an error with codes.Unknown when the error implements the GRPCStatus() method, and calling GRPCStatus() returns nil. (#6374)

Release 1.56.1

  • client: handle empty address lists correctly in addrConn.updateAddrs

Release 1.56.0

New Features

  • client: support channel idleness using WithIdleTimeout dial option (#6263)
    • This feature is currently disabled by default, but will be enabled with a 30 minute default in the future.
  • client: when using pickfirst, keep channel state in TRANSIENT_FAILURE until it becomes READY (gRFC A62) (#6306)
  • xds: Add support for Custom LB Policies (gRFC A52) (#6224)
  • xds: support pick_first Custom LB policy (gRFC A62) (#6314) (#6317)
  • client: add support for pickfirst address shuffling (gRFC A62) (#6311)
  • xds: Add support for String Matcher Header Matcher in RDS (#6313)
  • xds/outlierdetection: Add Channelz Logger to Outlier Detection LB (#6145)
    • Special Thanks: @​s-matyukevich
  • xds: enable RLS in xDS by default (#6343)
  • orca: add support for application_utilization field and missing range checks on several metrics setters
  • balancer/weightedroundrobin: add new LB policy for balancing between backends based on their load reports (gRFC A58) (#6241)
  • authz: add conversion of json to RBAC Audit Logging config (#6192)
  • authz: add support for stdout logger (#6230 and #6298)
  • authz: support customizable audit functionality for authorization policy (#6192 #6230 #6298 #6158 #6304 and #6225)

Bug Fixes

  • orca: fix a race at startup of out-of-band metric subscriptions that would cause the report interval to request 0 (#6245)
  • xds/xdsresource: Fix Outlier Detection Config Handling and correctly set xDS Defaults (#6361)
  • xds/outlierdetection: Fix Outlier Detection Config Handling by setting defaults in ParseConfig() (#6361)

API Changes

  • orca: allow a ServerMetricsProvider to be passed to the ORCA service and ServerOption (#6223)

Release 1.55.1

  • status: To fix a panic, status.FromError now returns an error with codes.Unknown when the error implements the GRPCStatus() method, and calling GRPCStatus() returns nil. (#6374)
Commits
  • 1055b48 Update version.go to 1.56.3 (#6713)
  • 5efd7bd server: prohibit more than MaxConcurrentStreams handlers from running at once...
  • bd1f038 Upgrade version.go to 1.56.3-dev (#6434)
  • faab873 Update version.go to v1.56.2 (#6432)
  • 6b0b291 status: fix panic when servers return a wrapped error with status OK (#6374) ...
  • ed56401 [PSM interop] Don't fail target if sub-target already failed (#6390) (#6405)
  • cd6a794 Update version.go to v1.56.2-dev (#6387)
  • 5b67e5e Update version.go to v1.56.1 (#6386)
  • d0f5150 client: handle empty address lists correctly in addrConn.updateAddrs (#6354) ...
  • 997c1ea Change version to 1.56.1-dev (#6345)
  • Additional commits viewable in compare view

issue.title: Support needed for Terragrunt Optional Dependencies

labels.name: infracost team
labels.description: These issues will be handled by the core Infracost team

issue.body:
Infracost on the latest version is not able to process the new "optional dependencies" feature of Terragrunt released in version [v0.50.17](https://github.com/gruntwork-io/terragrunt/releases/tag/v0.50.17)
- Added enabled property on dependency block, once set to false - dependency will be skipped.

If the enabled flag is used in a Terragrunt dependency in a terragrunt.hcl file, it results in the following error:

`Unsupported argument; An argument named "enabled" is not expected here.`

Here is an example of how the new feature is used:

```
dependency "sql_server" {
  enabled = local.environment_vars.locals.deploy_sql == "yes" ? true : false
  config_path = "../../sqlserver/sqlserver01"
  mock_outputs = {
    sql_server_id   = "/subscriptions/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/resourceGroups/mock-rg/providers/Microsoft.Sql/servers/mock-sql"
    sql_server_fqdn = "bdous-nc-devtest-mock-sql.database.net"
    sql_server_name = "mocksqlname"
  }
  mock_outputs_allowed_terraform_commands = ["validate", "plan"]
  mock_outputs_merge_strategy_with_state  = "shallow"
}
```

comment.body: @bdorplatt this is fixed in master now as a result of https://github.com/infracost/infracost/pull/2708. This will go out in the next release (scheduled for next week).

issue.title: Terragrunt `generate` blocks are not evaluated

labels.name: next release
labels.description: Issue will be resolved with the next release of Infracost.

issue.body:
## Example

```
terraform {
  source = "..//modules/example"
}

inputs = {
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
  root_block_device_volume_size = 50
  block_device_volume_size = 100
  block_device_iops = 400
  
  hello_world_function_memory_size = 512
}

generate "ec2" {
  path      = "ec2.tf"
  if_exists = "overwrite"
  contents  = <<EOF
resource "aws_instance" "mytest" {
  ami           = "ami-674cbc1e"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
}
EOF
}
```

## Expected results

Infracost writes out the `ec2.tf` file to the `.infracost/.terragrunt-cache/xxx/modules/examples/ec2.tf` and includes the `aws_instance.mytest` in the result output.

## Actual results

Infracost doesn't write out the file to the Terragrunt cache and doesn't include the resource in the output.

## Notes

This will probably need some logic to handle how we use the Terragrunt cache across different projects that use the same modules.
